    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"453ccb88-df1a-59e5-889e-53c5c0c878f7","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/my-personal-blog/static/b4c0f03f957c360afe090335525136e0/4b190/books-and-technology.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.583333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/b4c0f03f957c360afe090335525136e0/8ac56/books-and-technology.webp 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/b4c0f03f957c360afe090335525136e0/d3be9/books-and-technology.webp 480w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/b4c0f03f957c360afe090335525136e0/d00b9/books-and-technology.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/b4c0f03f957c360afe090335525136e0/09b79/books-and-technology.jpg 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/b4c0f03f957c360afe090335525136e0/7cc5e/books-and-technology.jpg 480w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/b4c0f03f957c360afe090335525136e0/4b190/books-and-technology.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/my-personal-blog/static/b4c0f03f957c360afe090335525136e0/4b190/books-and-technology.jpg\"\n            alt=\"Source: Dreamstime\"\n            title=\"Source: Dreamstime\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<em>Source: <a href=\"https://www.dreamstime.com/dictionary-modern-library-web-archive-literature-digital-culture-vector-people-reading-books-using-technology-image137941857\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Dreamstime.com</a></em></p>\n<p>Hi folks, It has been a long time since my last post. It’s time to back to writing, better late than never(<strong>or better late than even later</strong>).</p>\n<p>Well, I’m here to talk about five books that helped me a lot in my career regarding <strong>decision making, strategies to solve problems, general knowledge, soft skills, and motivation</strong>.</p>\n<figure>\n\t<blockquote>\n\t\t<p>“A reader lives a thousand lives before he dies . . . The man who never reads lives only one.”</p>\n\t\t<footer>\n\t\t\t<cite>— George R.R. Martin.</cite>\n\t\t</footer>\n\t</blockquote>\n</figure>\n<p>I like to think that I’ve anticipated a lot of problems and I’ve learned valuable lessons reading these books below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#the-passionate-programmer-creating-a-remarkable-career-in-software-development\">The Passionate Programmer: Creating a Remarkable Career in Software Development</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#the-pragmatic-programmer---your-journey-to-mastery(20th-anniversary-edition)\">The Pragmatic Programmer - your journey to mastery(20th Anniversary Edition)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#unwritten-laws-of-engineering---second-edition\">Unwritten Laws of Engineering - Second Edition</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#remote-office-not-required\">Remote: Office Not Required</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#explain-the-cloud-like-im-10\">Explain the Cloud Like I’m 10</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"let-me-explain-a-little-bit-about-how-each-of-these-books-helped-me\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#let-me-explain-a-little-bit-about-how-each-of-these-books-helped-me\" aria-label=\"let me explain a little bit about how each of these books helped me permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Let me explain a little bit about how each of these books helped me…</h3>\n<p><img src=\"https://media.giphy.com/media/XoW4aVP3LhBaoB7FuJ/giphy.gif\" alt=\"Alt Text\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"the-passionate-programmer-creating-a-remarkable-career-in-software-development\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-passionate-programmer-creating-a-remarkable-career-in-software-development\" aria-label=\"the passionate programmer creating a remarkable career in software development permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Passionate Programmer: Creating a Remarkable Career in Software Development</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 333px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/my-personal-blog/static/5db8fac77b9f0e441c50168903edea9d/77c11/the-passionate-programmer(cover).jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 150%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/5db8fac77b9f0e441c50168903edea9d/8ac56/the-passionate-programmer(cover).webp 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/5db8fac77b9f0e441c50168903edea9d/f885a/the-passionate-programmer(cover).webp 333w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 333px) 100vw, 333px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/5db8fac77b9f0e441c50168903edea9d/09b79/the-passionate-programmer(cover).jpg 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/5db8fac77b9f0e441c50168903edea9d/77c11/the-passionate-programmer(cover).jpg 333w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 333px) 100vw, 333px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/my-personal-blog/static/5db8fac77b9f0e441c50168903edea9d/77c11/the-passionate-programmer(cover).jpg\"\n            alt=\"The Passionate Programmer: Creating a Remarkable Career in Software Development\"\n            title=\"The Passionate Programmer: Creating a Remarkable Career in Software Development\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<em>Source: <a href=\"https://images.app.goo.gl/Ya2PZMqa3n9NNzbE8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Amazon</a></em></p>\n<p>I really <strong>love</strong> this book by <strong>Chad Fowler</strong>. I read it in a period in which I was struggling to grow in my career, working in a very toxic environment, and dazed and confused about what I was looking for in the software development world.</p>\n<p>At that time I was asking myself: What should I study now? Am I a full-stack developer? Should I focus on backend? Or frontend? What programming languages should I learn? <strong>This book has helped me a lot to answer all of these questions</strong>.</p>\n<p>The book is strictly about career development and it has a lot of insights about how to perform better as a programmer and explore the best opportunities for you. With this book, I discovered how much I really love to work with programming and it has opened my eyes to some ways to improve.</p>\n<h2 id=\"the-pragmatic-programmer---your-journey-to-mastery20th-anniversary-edition\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-pragmatic-programmer---your-journey-to-mastery20th-anniversary-edition\" aria-label=\"the pragmatic programmer   your journey to mastery20th anniversary edition permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Pragmatic Programmer - your journey to mastery(20th Anniversary Edition)</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 459px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/my-personal-blog/static/891b67505b7862ba5b11c4f03b63f45e/a3b4c/the-pragmatic-programmer-your-journey-to-mastery.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 130.83333333333334%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/891b67505b7862ba5b11c4f03b63f45e/8ac56/the-pragmatic-programmer-your-journey-to-mastery.webp 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/891b67505b7862ba5b11c4f03b63f45e/25604/the-pragmatic-programmer-your-journey-to-mastery.webp 459w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 459px) 100vw, 459px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/891b67505b7862ba5b11c4f03b63f45e/09b79/the-pragmatic-programmer-your-journey-to-mastery.jpg 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/891b67505b7862ba5b11c4f03b63f45e/a3b4c/the-pragmatic-programmer-your-journey-to-mastery.jpg 459w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 459px) 100vw, 459px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/my-personal-blog/static/891b67505b7862ba5b11c4f03b63f45e/a3b4c/the-pragmatic-programmer-your-journey-to-mastery.jpg\"\n            alt=\"The Pragmatic Programmer - your journey to mastery(20th Anniversary Edition)\"\n            title=\"The Pragmatic Programmer - your journey to mastery(20th Anniversary Edition)\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<em>Source: <a href=\"https://images.app.goo.gl/iZCcYsJFcKYTujMF8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Amazon</a></em></p>\n<p>A masterpiece by <strong>David Thomas</strong> and <strong>Andrew Hunt</strong>. This book is about career development too, showing topics ranging from <strong>personal responsibility and career development to architectural techniques for keeping your code flexible and easy to adapt and reuse</strong>.</p>\n<p>The book is filled with classic and fresh anecdotes, thoughtful examples, and very interesting analogies. I’ve learned and developed skills, habits, and attitudes from this book and formed a foundation for the long term. I really think that <strong>pragmatism is a core skill for a software engineer</strong> and this book was fundamental for me to develop it.</p>\n<p>I strongly suggest the latest edition because it is using examples with updated technology and terminology.</p>\n<h2 id=\"unwritten-laws-of-engineering---second-edition\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#unwritten-laws-of-engineering---second-edition\" aria-label=\"unwritten laws of engineering   second edition permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Unwritten Laws of Engineering - Second Edition</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 328px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/my-personal-blog/static/d97f04d2867246294b8cac71182d83a9/adebe/the-unwritten-laws-of-engineering(cover).jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 152.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/d97f04d2867246294b8cac71182d83a9/8ac56/the-unwritten-laws-of-engineering(cover).webp 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/d97f04d2867246294b8cac71182d83a9/1009d/the-unwritten-laws-of-engineering(cover).webp 328w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 328px) 100vw, 328px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/d97f04d2867246294b8cac71182d83a9/09b79/the-unwritten-laws-of-engineering(cover).jpg 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/d97f04d2867246294b8cac71182d83a9/adebe/the-unwritten-laws-of-engineering(cover).jpg 328w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 328px) 100vw, 328px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/my-personal-blog/static/d97f04d2867246294b8cac71182d83a9/adebe/the-unwritten-laws-of-engineering(cover).jpg\"\n            alt=\"Unwritten Laws of Engineering - Second Edition\"\n            title=\"Unwritten Laws of Engineering - Second Edition\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<em>Source: <a href=\"https://images.app.goo.gl/SEVHbuMCVc4wPabb8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Amazon</a></em></p>\n<p>The oldest book here. A classic written by <strong>W. J. King</strong> in 1944. A book with a message so timeless, so universal, that it transcends generations. Good news: <em>it’s a revised and updated edition, so don’t mind about unused terminologies or having a very struggling reading</em>.</p>\n<p>This book is amazing to understand the corporate structure and how you should behave to improve your professional effectiveness. The book isn’t about acting like a corp robot but rather about keeping in mind some directives that are going to facilitate your job and the projects that you are working on, considering the nature of the job, your supervisor, your relations, the products involved, your career, and your behavior.</p>\n<p>This book transcends the engineering field and its concepts could be applied to every occupation I guess.</p>\n<h2 id=\"remote-office-not-required\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#remote-office-not-required\" aria-label=\"remote office not required permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Remote: Office Not Required</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 354px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/my-personal-blog/static/d9c8a05685bf7ded09af53c2c0734c92/e1632/remote-office-not-required(cover).jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 141.25%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/d9c8a05685bf7ded09af53c2c0734c92/8ac56/remote-office-not-required(cover).webp 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/d9c8a05685bf7ded09af53c2c0734c92/7d039/remote-office-not-required(cover).webp 354w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 354px) 100vw, 354px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/d9c8a05685bf7ded09af53c2c0734c92/09b79/remote-office-not-required(cover).jpg 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/d9c8a05685bf7ded09af53c2c0734c92/e1632/remote-office-not-required(cover).jpg 354w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 354px) 100vw, 354px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/my-personal-blog/static/d9c8a05685bf7ded09af53c2c0734c92/e1632/remote-office-not-required(cover).jpg\"\n            alt=\"Remote - Office not required\"\n            title=\"Remote - Office not required\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<em>Source: <a href=\"https://images.app.goo.gl/4kufdZp5Cc8Kf45H6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Amazon</a></em></p>\n<p>This book by <strong>David Heinemeier Hansson</strong> and <strong>Jason Fried</strong> helped me a lot in the 2020’s COVID pandemic (and it’s still helping). <strong>I’m not a big fan of remote work</strong>, and when the pandemic started I really worried about my performance at my job because I’ve never worked this way before.</p>\n<p>Be aware that you’re not going to be delighted by scientific evidence about doing this or that. <strong>It’s a very opinionated book, presenting the empiric knowledge about what worked(and is still working) for <a href=\"https://37signals.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">37 signals</a> as a fully remote company.</strong></p>\n<p>Although some of the situations presented sometimes seem exaggerated, for me it was possible to draw a parallel with my reality and apply many of the ideas to my work routine.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, this book is very valuable for communication at all with very valuable tips that you can apply even if you’re not working remotely.</p>\n<p>Another very good source of knowledge about it is <a href=\"https://basecamp.com/guides/how-we-communicate\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The Basecamp Guide to Internal Communication</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"explain-the-cloud-like-im-10\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#explain-the-cloud-like-im-10\" aria-label=\"explain the cloud like im 10 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Explain the Cloud Like I’m 10</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 333px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/my-personal-blog/static/c1f3e1c4515e8da843348effa4970888/77c11/explain-cloud-like-im-10-years-old.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 150%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/c1f3e1c4515e8da843348effa4970888/8ac56/explain-cloud-like-im-10-years-old.webp 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/c1f3e1c4515e8da843348effa4970888/f885a/explain-cloud-like-im-10-years-old.webp 333w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 333px) 100vw, 333px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/my-personal-blog/static/c1f3e1c4515e8da843348effa4970888/09b79/explain-cloud-like-im-10-years-old.jpg 240w,\n/my-personal-blog/static/c1f3e1c4515e8da843348effa4970888/77c11/explain-cloud-like-im-10-years-old.jpg 333w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 333px) 100vw, 333px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/my-personal-blog/static/c1f3e1c4515e8da843348effa4970888/77c11/explain-cloud-like-im-10-years-old.jpg\"\n            alt=\"Explain the Cloud Like I&#39;m 10\"\n            title=\"Explain the Cloud Like I&#39;m 10\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<em>Source: <a href=\"https://images.app.goo.gl/9U4JUST45LGj2rhX8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Amazon</a></em></p>\n<p><strong>Just brilliant</strong>. This book by <strong>Todd Hoff</strong> presents some very interesting and complex concepts about networks, cloud services and it explains what happens under the hood when you watch something on a huge streaming service like Netflix.</p>\n<p>Not only having these hard concepts being explained in a very enjoyable way to read but <strong>this book has also opened my mind about presenting content</strong>. The terminology, the images, the analogies, all of these aspects in this book have helped a lot to make my own presentations.</p>\n<p><strong>Explaining complex concepts through flow-diagrams and alike has increased a lot of my skills and my impact on the teams I’ve worked on</strong>. Lots of tips on how to do that I borrowed from this great book.</p>\n<p>This book is amazing for software developers and it’s even more important for non-technical people. <strong>I truly believe that this is a book for everyone</strong>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"thats-all-folks\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#thats-all-folks\" aria-label=\"thats all folks permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><strong>That’s all folks</strong>.</h3>\n<p>Hope you’ve enjoyed this list. Reading has been fundamental for my professional and personal growth. I hope these recommendations help you too.</p>\n<p>Which books were important to your career?</p>\n<p>*<em>Thanks to <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/marcelbornancin/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Marcel Bornancin</a> for the review.</em></p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/five-books-that-changed-my-career-as-a-software-engineer","tagSlugs":["/tag/reading/","/tag/books/","/tag/career/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-11-27T22:40:32.169Z","description":"I'd like to present five books that have changed my mind about software development showing me lots of concepts, techniques and tips. Let's see them and why I they were so valuable to me","tags":["Reading","Books","Career"],"title":"Five Books that Changed My Career as a Software Engineer","socialImage":"/media/books-and-technology.jpeg"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/five-books-that-changed-my-career-as-a-software-engineer"}},
